latestIgtvVideos.title: Tie & dye dress styling video
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#thefashionchariot - Tie and dye fashion trend has been around since forever, but this awesome trend has recently made a comeback as one of the biggest fashion trends of #2020 .

It was observed as a huge trend on the spring/summer 2020 fashion shows/ramp & it has continued to make a big and bold style statement in lockdown fashion. Clearly a #throwback to the 1960s & 1970s, tie&dye has to some extent,in my eyes, replaced florals for the trend of the season both on Instagram and shopping platforms. 

Whether you look at it as a DIY style or we purchase an item, there are plenty of ways to wear the colorful trend. 

I have rounded up 4 of my different styles/lookw to wear a classic tie&dye slip dress 😄

latestPosts.caption:
Turning old shades into new Faves 💄✨

Yes, you heard it right. I store my lipsticks based on how pigmented they are 💄🤩 

And let me tell you why: it makes it easy to reach my favorites and mix them up to create new shades with the ones I already own 🙌 This way, I never get bored or leave them unused just because they don’t suit me solo. Isn’t that amazing? 🤍🤍

In this video, we dive into the 3 lipstick shades challenge! 💄💄💄 I’m picking three random shades— to create something unexpectedly gorgeous and wearable. 

I’m wearing a layer of concealer on my lips before applying lip color. It creates a clear canvas, reduces pigmentation and makes the original lip color pop! ✨ 
This shade is so close to ‘All Fired Up’ from @maccosmeticsindia 
If you loved this hack, drop a thank you in the comments! 🫶🏻🫶🏻☺️☺️

Lipsticks used in the video -
Surrender - Air matte lipstick @narsissist 
Bombae @nykaacosmetics 
Old school - lip sensation lipstick @paccosmetic 

#threelipsticktchallenge #threeinoneliptrend #lipsticklover #beautyhacks #lipsticktutorial
